Jeff Goodman polls NBA execs: Don't trade Wiggins Unlike "The Decision," LeBron James' returning to the Cleveland Cavaliers as a free agent last Friday doesn't immediately create a star-studded big three. However, one more transaction -- the Cavaliers dealing for Minnesota Timberwolves star Kevin Love -- would bring together a trio of players, including Cleveland incumbent Kyrie Irving, that would have the potential to surpass the threesome that helped the Miami Heat reach the NBA Finals four times and win two championships.